			<p uri="/ensign/2001/11/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ.p77" class="">Again in English: I know the gospel is true and that Jesus is the Christ.</p>
			<p uri="/ensign/2001/11/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ.p78" class="">I love this Book of Mormon: Another Testament of Jesus Christ. Study it and one can understand both the Old Testament and the New Testament in the Bible. I know it is true.</p>
			<p uri="/ensign/2001/11/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ.p79" class="">In this 1830 edition of the Book of Mormon, printed by 23-year-old Egbert B. Grandin for 23-year-old Joseph Smith Jr., I read from page 105: &ldquo;We talk of Christ, we rejoice in Christ, we <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/library/display/0,4945,8057-1-4424-1,00.html">preach</a> of Christ, we prophesy of Christ, and we write according to our prophecies, that our children may know to what source they may look for a remission of their sins.&rdquo;<sup class="noteMarker">
	<a href="#footnote20-21911_000_025">20</a>
      </sup></p>
			<p uri="/ensign/2001/11/the-book-of-mormon-another-testament-of-jesus-christ.p80" class="">And that, I assure you, is exactly what we do. In the name of Jesus Christ, amen.</p>
		
                            
                            
